The paper presents a new approach to path planning for robots with many degrees of freedom in both static and dynamic environments. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the algorithm involves optimization problems, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The use of a moving obstacle in the experiments suggests that the paper could also be relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
